{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.17",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 17,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 17 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:1",
      "text": "The Lord created mankind out of earth, and turned them back to it again.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:2",
      "text": "He gave them days by number, and a set time, and gave them authority over the things that are on it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:3",
      "text": "He endowed them with strength proper to them, and made them according to his own image.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:4",
      "text": "He put the fear of man upon all flesh, and gave him dominion over beasts and birds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:6",
      "text": "He gave them counsel, tongue, eyes, ears, and heart to have understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:7",
      "text": "He filled them with the knowledge of wisdom, and showed them good and evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:8",
      "text": "He set his eye upon their hearts, to show them the majesty of his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:10",
      "text": "And they will praise his holy name, that they may declare the majesty of his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:11",
      "text": "He added to them knowledge, and gave them a law of life for a heritage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:12",
      "text": "He made an everlasting covenant with them, and showed them his decrees.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:13",
      "text": "Their eyes saw the majesty of his glory. Their ears heard the glory of his voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:14",
      "text": "He said to them, “Beware of all unrighteousness.” So he gave them commandment, each man concerning his neighbor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:15",
      "text": "Their ways are ever before him. They will not be hidden from his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:17",
      "text": "For every nation he appointed a ruler, but Israel is the Lord’s portion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:19",
      "text": "All their works are as clear as the sun before him. His eyes are continually upon their ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:20",
      "text": "Their iniquities are not hidden from him. All their sins are before the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:22",
      "text": "With him the alms of a man is as a signet. He will keep a man’s kindness as the pupil of the eye.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:23",
      "text": "Afterwards he will rise up and repay them, and give their repayment upon their head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:24",
      "text": "However to those who repent he grants a return. He comforts those who are losing hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:25",
      "text": "Return to the Lord, and forsake sins. Make your prayer before his face offend less.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:26",
      "text": "Turn again to the Most High, and turn away from iniquity. Greatly hate the abominable thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:27",
      "text": "Who will give praise to the Most High in Hades, in place of the living who return thanks?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:28",
      "text": "Thanksgiving perishes from the dead, as from one who doesn’t exist. He who is in life and health will praise the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:29",
      "text": "How great is the mercy of the Lord, and his forgiveness to those who turn to him!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:30",
      "text": "For humans are not capable of everything, because the son of man is not immortal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:31",
      "text": "What is brighter than the sun? Yet even this can be eclipsed. So flesh and blood devise evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.17.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:32",
      "text": "He looks upon the power of the height of heaven, while all men are earth and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
